						<summary>

						<p>Pillar built into the wall of the southern entrance to the inner <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1525, (expired) Śōbhakṛit, Bhādrapada śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1602 A.D., August 22, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of some shrines and halls probably in the Mallikārjuna temple by Haṇḍe Ḍēmappa Nāyaniṅgāru.</p>						

						</summary>
